---
import ComponentDoc from '../../layouts/ComponentDoc.astro';
import Section from '../../components/docs/Section.astro';
import Preview from '../../components/docs/Preview.astro';
import Api from '../../components/docs/Api.astro';
import FormField from '@esa/ecology/esa-form-field.astro';

const props = [
  { name: 'label', type: 'string', default: "''", description: 'Label rendered above the control slot.' },
  { name: 'helpText', type: 'string', default: "''", description: 'Helper text shown below the control.' },
  { name: 'errorText', type: 'string', default: "''", description: 'Error message; replaces help text when present.' },
  { name: 'required', type: 'boolean', default: 'false', description: 'Renders an asterisk on the label.' },
  { name: 'disabled', type: 'boolean', default: 'false', description: 'Dims the field and blocks pointer events.' },
  { name: 'size', type: "'xs' | 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg'", default: "'md'", description: 'Scales the label font size.' },
];
---
<ComponentDoc name="Form Field" category="Forms" slug="esa-form-field" type=".astro" status="stable"
  summary="A presentational layout wrapper — label row, control slot, and hint/error text. Pure <code>.astro</code> with no runtime JS; drop any control into the slot. Error text replaces help text when present.">

  <Section id="preview" title="Preview">
    <Preview code={`<FormField label="Email" helpText="We will never share your email.">
  <input type="email" placeholder="you@example.com" />
</FormField>`}>
      <FormField label="Email" helpText="We will never share your email.">
        <input type="email" class="demo-input" placeholder="you@example.com" />
      </FormField>
    </Preview>
  </Section>

  <Section id="states" title="States">
    <p>Mark a field <code>required</code>, surface an <code>errorText</code> in place of help text, or <code>disabled</code> the whole field.</p>
    <Preview code={`<FormField label="Project name" required>
  <input type="text" />
</FormField>

<FormField label="Permit ID" errorText="Permit ID is required." required>
  <input type="text" aria-invalid="true" />
</FormField>

<FormField label="Locked field" helpText="This field cannot be edited." disabled>
  <input type="text" disabled value="Read only" />
</FormField>`}>
      <div class="col">
        <FormField label="Project name" required={true}>
          <input type="text" class="demo-input" />
        </FormField>
        <FormField label="Permit ID" errorText="Permit ID is required." required={true}>
          <input type="text" aria-invalid="true" class="demo-input demo-input--error" />
        </FormField>
        <FormField label="Locked field" helpText="This field cannot be edited." disabled={true}>
          <input type="text" disabled value="Read only" class="demo-input demo-input--disabled" />
        </FormField>
      </div>
    </Preview>
  </Section>

  <Section id="sizes" title="Sizes">
    <p>The <code>size</code> prop scales the label; size the control yourself to match.</p>
    <Preview code={`<FormField label="Extra small label" size="xs"> … </FormField>
<FormField label="Small label" size="sm"> … </FormField>
<FormField label="Medium label" size="md"> … </FormField>
<FormField label="Large label" size="lg"> … </FormField>`}>
      <div class="col">
        <FormField label="Extra small label" size="xs">
          <input type="text" class="demo-input demo-input--xs" />
        </FormField>
        <FormField label="Small label" size="sm">
          <input type="text" class="demo-input demo-input--sm" />
        </FormField>
        <FormField label="Medium label" size="md">
          <input type="text" class="demo-input" />
        </FormField>
        <FormField label="Large label" size="lg">
          <input type="text" class="demo-input demo-input--lg" />
        </FormField>
      </div>
    </Preview>
  </Section>

  <Section id="api" title="API">
    <Api props={props} />
    <p>The control goes in the default slot — the wrapper makes no assumptions about it.</p>
  </Section>

  <Section id="accessibility" title="Accessibility">
    <ul class="a11y">
      <li>The wrapper is presentational only; associate the label and control yourself (e.g. a <code>for</code>/<code>id</code> pair) since the slot content is opaque to it.</li>
      <li>The required asterisk carries an <code>aria-label="required"</code>.</li>
      <li>Set <code>aria-invalid="true"</code> on the slotted control whenever <code>errorText</code> is shown.</li>
      <li><code>disabled</code> dims the field and blocks pointer events; also disable the underlying control for keyboard users.</li>
    </ul>
  </Section>

  <Section id="tokens" title="Tokens">
    <p>The wrapper maps these public tokens onto private <code>--_*</code> tokens with fallbacks:</p>
    <ul class="tokens">
      <li><code>--form-label-color</code> · <code>--form-help-color</code> · <code>--form-error-color</code></li>
      <li><code>--form-font-size-small</code> / <code>--form-font-size-medium</code> / <code>--form-font-size-large</code> (label scale)</li>
      <li><code>--form-label-gap</code> · <code>--form-help-gap</code> · <code>--type-size-100</code> (help/error size)</li>
      <li><code>--font-weight-medium</code> · <code>--color-danger</code> (required asterisk)</li>
    </ul>
  </Section>
</ComponentDoc>

<style>
  .col { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--spacing-500, 1.5rem); width: 100%; max-width: 360px; }
  .demo-input {
    width: 100%;
    height: 40px;
    padding: 0 0.75rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border, #e5e5e5);
    border-radius: var(--radius-200, 0.5rem);
    font: inherit;
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }
  .demo-input--error { border-color: var(--color-danger, #ef4444); }
  .demo-input--disabled { background: var(--form-bg-disabled, #efefef); }
  .demo-input--xs { height: 28px; padding: 0 0.5rem; border-radius: var(--radius-100, 0.25rem); }
  .demo-input--sm { height: 32px; padding: 0 0.5rem; border-radius: var(--radius-100, 0.25rem); }
  .demo-input--lg { height: 48px; padding: 0 1rem; border-radius: var(--radius-300, 0.75rem); }
</style>
